This paper deals with the analysis of user reviews of mobile apps, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), which deals with the retrieval and analysis of information from unstructured data sources such as text. 

The paper also involves the use of keyword-based approaches and semantic representations, which are common in sub-categories such as cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

The paper also deals with the detection of sudden changes in trends, which is related to sub-categories such as cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SE (Software Engineering), which deal with the social and ethical implications of software systems.
